            <p>The Kops mss. II, 1950-1983, consists of the correspondence and writings of British dramatist and poet Bernard Kops, 1926- . The writings present include plays; novels; broadcast talks; a television drama; a film treatment; poems, both published and unpublished; notebooks dating from 1950 to 1980; and his autobiography, <title render="doublequote">The World is a Wedding.</title></p>
